@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Help";
}
<h2>Help guide</h2>

<hr />

<h3>Flight Search page</h3>

<p>
    On the Flight Search page you can search flights using one of three flight types.
    You can choose beetwen them using radio button in the middle of the page.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>One Way flights</h3>

<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <img src="~/Content/flight details.png" class="img-responsive">
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <img src="~/Content/flight back details.png" class="img-responsive" />
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>
    In one way flight mode you can only specify first flight details. Flight back details are read only.
    From and To locations are text fields where you can input city names without any numbers and special characters.
    You can choose date using datepicker. You can choose to skip date. Numbers of passengers are number fields
    where you can write numbers or use arrows on the right.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Round trip standard flights</h3>

<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <img src="~/Content/flight details round trip standard.png" class="img-responsive">
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <img src="~/Content/flight back details round trip standard.png" class="img-responsive" />
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>
    In round trip standard flight mode you can specify first flight details and date, skip date, direct
    flight back fields. Other flight back details inputs will be automatically updated using first flight
    inputs values. In this mode you can input values the same way you did in the first mode.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Round trip non-standard flights</h3>

<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <img src="~/Content/flight details round trip non standard.png" class="img-responsive">
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
        <img src="~/Content/flight back details round trip non standard.png" class="img-responsive" />
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>
    In round trip non-standard flight mode you can specify first flight details and flight back details.
    This gives you opportunity to choose other return city or diffrent number of passengers.
    In this mode you can input values the same way you did in the first mode.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Form validation</h3>

<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-12">
        <img src="~/Content/flight search validation.png" class="img-responsive">
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>
    If you will put values in wrong format, you will get nottification about it. The input in which values are
    in incorrect format will have red border and on the right there will be red text with information about what
    is wrong.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Flight Search result</h3>

<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-12">
        <img src="~/Content/flight search result.png" class="img-responsive">
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>
    When you input flight details in a correct format and then click on Search button, you will be
    redirected to the result page. On this page you will find flight details and flights which our
    site found. Each flight is presented in card format with information like price, date, flight time
    airlne logo, flight number. You will also find Check button which redirects you to page where
    you can find similar flight and buy tickets.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Flight Ideas page</h3>

<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-12">
        <img src="~/Content/flight ideas main.png" class="img-responsive">
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>
    On the Flight Ideas page you can find suggestions for flights to popular destinations.
    If you want to find suggestions only from given city, you can use form at the top of this
    page. Flights which are found by our site are presented in the same format as at
    Flight Search result page.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Contact page</h3>

<hr />

<p>
    On the Contact page you can find contact information which you can use to ask us questions, give us
    reviews or report some issues.
</p>
